Summary: toPandas() crashes with SIGSEGV on nested empty arrays
Status: Resolved

{{toPandas()}} crashes with SIGSEGV when a DataFrame contains nested array types (depth >= 3) with an empty outer array.
{code:python}
schema = StructType([
    StructField("data", ArrayType(StructType([
        StructField("arr", ArrayType(StructType([
            StructField("inner", ArrayType(StringType()))
        ])))
    ])))
])
df = spark.createDataFrame([Row(data=[])], schema=schema)
df.toPandas()  # SIGSEGV
{code}
Arrow format requires ListArray offset buffer to have N+1 entries. Even when N=0, the buffer must contain {{{}[0]{}}}. When the outer array is empty, nested {{ArrayWriters are never invoked, so their count}} stays 0. Then {{getBufferSizeFor(0)}} returns 0, and the offset buffer is omitted in IPC serialization — violating Arrow spec.
{code:scala}
// ArrayWriter.scala - current behavior
override def setValue(...): Unit = {
  while (i < array.numElements()) {  // never runs when empty
    elementWriter.write(array, i)    // nested writer never called
  }
}
{code}

